Letter 102. 8. domine: this word was used in polite address to all classes of persons, sometimes even by superiors to inferiors. The early tendency to make it an official title of the emperors was checked by Augustus and Tiberius, and it seems to have been a couple of cen- turies before it became a regular official title.
